text.p: Port conditions from Lloyds Shipping Intelligence Service --
AUSTRALIA, Oct 14 - COAL - QUEENSLAND - Abbot Point - Berth vacant, 9 vessels due by 23/11, no delays.
Dalrymple Bay - One vessel loading, 2 waiting, 15 vessels due by 24/10. Approx. 1-2 days delay. Maintenance shutdown scheduled for 4/11 to 9/11.
Hay Point - Two vessels loading, 6 waiting, 5 due by 20/10. Berths 1 and 2 were closed from 1900 hours 9/10 to 0600 hours 10/10 due to strong wind and heavy seas.

Gladstone - Barney Point - No vessels due to major shutdown to upgrade terminals plant and equipment. First train arrived at Barney Point for unloading 11/10. First vessel to load scheduled for approx. 10/11.
R.G. Tanna - 2 Vessels loading, 5 waiting, 24 due by 25/11, approx. 2-3 days delay.
NEW SOUTH WALES - Newcastle - Kooragang - 2 Vessels loading, 8 waiting, 5 due by 28/10, approx. 4-5 days delay. Dyke 4+5 - 2 Vessels loading, 2 waiting, 17 due by 28/10, approx. 1-2 days delay.
Port Kembla - Berth vacant, 17 vessels due 3/11, no delays.
IRON ORE - Port Hedland - Mt. Newman (Nelson Point) - Berth a - 1 Vessel loading, 1 anchored, 6 due by 21/10. Berth b - 1 Vessel loading, 7 due by 20/10, 7 other vessels due with no eta.
Dampier - Parker Point - 1 Vessel loading, 1 anchored, 1 due 15/10.
Port Walcott - One vessel loading, 8 due by 28/10.
